Stephen Duffy recorded throughout the eighties, but this 1995 number grows on you.<br /><br /> <a href="http://www.youtube.com/v/apdVSCpj4qU"></param><param target="_blank"><strong>object</strong></a> <br /><br />The mezzo-soprano who cuts in at 3:30 is Penny Vickers, one of the mathematicians at Nine Tiles where the early ZX ROMs were written.<br />Penny wrote the BASIC example programs in the Spectrum manual which was mainly authored by her brother Steven.<br />Also a pamphlet for the Jupiter Ace showing how to program Newton Raphson square roots.<br /><br />She has recorded lots of vinyl and CDs from Lennon/McCartney in the early 80s to madrigals and motets with the BBC Singers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=69">warmtoffee</a> — Mon Aug 08, 2011 10:58 am — Replies 0 — Views 358</p><hr />
