<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Games • First Game You Loaded Onto A Spectrum?]]></title>

<category term="The Games" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=5" label="The Games"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=29&amp;p=93#p93"><![CDATA[
Pangolins does not count...<br /><br />So then, can you recall what the first game was that you loaded onto your Spectrum?  What were you first impressions - what are your thoughts of the game now?<br /><br />I can recall vividly the first time a game was loaded onto my computer because it wasn't me that did it. I returned from school to find my new (birthday present) Spectrum unwrapped and in use with my mum's boyfriend at the helm!  He was playing Mountains of Ket by Incentive and the initial indignation of my present being opened by somebody else passed quickly as we both attempted to (if I recall correctly) kill a dwarf with an axe.  I was transfixed with the game despite being non-plussed at the lack of graphics, and it started an on/off love affair that I have had with text adventures ever since. One of these days I will actually complete one of them.  <br /><br />As with most games from that era, time has been a harsh judge. I have attempted to play the game on an emulator but find myself becoming quickly frustrated at not being able to make myself understood - perhaps this is merely a sign of me disintegrating into a curmudgeonly Victor Meldrewesque character rather than any fault of the game.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=77">Meurglys68</a> — Sat Jul 02, 2011 6:39 pm — Replies 7 — Views 860</p><hr />
]]></content>
