<id>http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=28&amp;p=89#p89</id>
<link href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=28&amp;p=89#p89"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Sinclair Misc • What we had to put up with!]]></title>

<category term="Sinclair Misc" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=6" label="Sinclair Misc"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=28&amp;p=89#p89"><![CDATA[
It's amazing what we take for granted today - free word processors with smooth antialiased fonts, for instance. I used to use Tasword Two on the Speccy - no fonts, each character was three (yes, THREE) pixels wide, no other typefaces (not even bold or italics) were shown onscreen. Instead we had to make do with putting in block graphics characters to mark the start and end of each bit of formatted text, and we were grateful for that!<br /><br />What other things did we put up with back then which would be unthinkable today?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=73">Chuckie</a> — Sat Jul 02, 2011 6:10 pm — Replies 9 — Views 1066</p><hr />
]]></content>
