<category term="The Games" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=5" label="The Games"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=27&amp;p=84#p84"><![CDATA[
It Christmas Day 1987, I eagerly rip open my Xmas presents to find the holy grail of arcade games at the time - Out Run !!<br /><br />The screen-shots on the back cover whetted my appetite, after 3 to 4 failed attempts to load (dodgy ear to ear wire) the game loaded and the famous theme tunes played out, then the game played -  <img src="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/images/smilies/icon_eek.gif" alt=":shock:" title="Shocked" />  followed by  <img src="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" />  followed by  <img src="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/images/smilies/icon_cry.gif" alt=":cry:" title="Crying or Very Sad" /> . Football Manager had sprites that moved faster and then to cap it off it was followed followed by a multi load.<br /><br />This and World Cup Carnival - I never trusted US Gold again.<br /><br />Any one else with games that were massive let-downs ?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=86">Ritman_Utd</a> — Sat Jul 02, 2011 3:26 pm — Replies 18 — Views 2615</p><hr />
