<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Games • The tail-enders]]></title>

<category term="The Games" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=5" label="The Games"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=22&amp;p=49#p49"><![CDATA[
Some people think that the Speccy games industry peaked in 1985, others like myself think the peak was 1988. What cannot be argued is that in 1991 the industry was going downhill fast. There are still a few gems from the '90s, though - I'm particularly fond of World Class Rugby, which was a fantastically well-executed rugby sim which was slick and very playable.<br /><br />So, which of the tail-enders impressed you most?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">NickH</a> — Sun Jun 26, 2011 5:27 pm — Replies 7 — Views 727</p><hr />
