<author><name><![CDATA[NickH]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-06-26T17:15:46+01:00</updated>
<id>http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=21&amp;p=48#p48</id>
<link href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=21&amp;p=48#p48"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Sinclair Misc • Introduce yourself!]]></title>

<category term="Sinclair Misc" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=6" label="Sinclair Misc"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=21&amp;p=48#p48"><![CDATA[
Don't be shy - tell us a bit about yourself! I'll start the ball rolling:<br /><br />I'm Nick Humphries, and I got my first Speccy in 1985 - it was one of the Spectrum+'s which was part of the Dixons deal which tided over Sinclair Research into 1986. I briefly owned a +2 before getting one of the doomed SAM Coupe's which seemed to have some sort of psychic link with whoever was making them at the time. Both times, when MGT and SAMCo went under, my SAM broke down!<br /><br />Your Sinclair was the first computer magazine that I ever bought - it was the June 1987 issue which I bought on the strength of its programming features, but once I saw the games features (including the delectable Head Over Heels which was Megagamed that issue) I was hooked on both it and the software scene. I was immediately sucked into the industry's hype machine and loved it. I stopped buying YS in 1992 because no shops near me would sell it by that time!<br /><br />I discovered the retroscene in December 1992 when I was pointed towards the SincNews email mailing list, and I've stayed with the scene as it passed on through the comp.sys.sinclair Usenet newsgroup and the World Of Spectrum forums. I set up the YSRnRY in 1997 as a sort of substitute for flicking through my original magazine collection over and over again, and helped set up The Tipshop in 2001 with Gerard Sweeney. All through this time I found joy in doing silly things in interesting ways, and I have found that surrounding myself with enthusiasts who love the subject both addictive and inspirational.<br /><br />Next year will be the 20th anniversary of my involvement in the scene. Yikes. 2012 is going to be a big year for me, website-wise.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">NickH</a> — Sun Jun 26, 2011 5:15 pm — Replies 7 — Views 829</p><hr />
]]></content>
