<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Your Sinclair Rock'n'Roll Years • Welcome to the forums!]]></title>

<category term="The Your Sinclair Rock'n'Roll Years" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=2" label="The Your Sinclair Rock'n'Roll Years"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=18&amp;p=45#p45"><![CDATA[
Welcome to the Your Sinclair Rock'n'Roll Years forum! We hope you'll stick around and have a bit of fun.<br /><br />There are the following forums available:<br /><br />Documentary/Site News: Here you'll be able to find out and discuss any YSRnRY-related activity, be it documentary development and feedback, or website additions. I'll also write the odd news piece with info from around the scene.<br /><br />Your Sinclair, and other animals: The place to be for discussion about Your Sinclair and its related magazines, such as Your Spectrum and Zero, plus magazines which were heavily influenced by YS, such as PC Zone.<br /><br />The Games: The best, the average, and the true blue stinkers - tell the world what you think of the games which appeared on the Sinclair and SAM computers!<br /><br />Sinclair Misc: Anything Sinclair-related which isn't covered by the other forums.<br /><br />1980's Nostalgia: Fancy a wallow in memories of yesteryear? Come here and dive in!<br /><br />Whilst there are no forum rules as such, these forums are moderated, and will be moderated in a way to keep everything fun and light. Obviously you can't describe a set of rules which will tell you what's &quot;good&quot; and what's &quot;bad&quot;, but a good starting point is &quot;Be Excellent To Each Other&quot;. One other guideline: try to keep the off-topic stuff to a minimum - we don't mind the odd off-topic post, but we don't want the forums flooded with them. <br /><br />Irish comedian Dara O Briain put it quite nicely when talking about the differences between Irish and British approaches to rules and regulations. Whereas the Brits are very prescriptive, the Irish have basically three vague classifications. All the good stuff is classed as &quot;That's grand&quot;. The grey areas are classed as &quot;Ah, now don't push it.&quot; And then when the lines are crossed, &quot;Right! You're taking the piss!&quot;, and they're dealt with. Moderation is done in private, and the moderator's decision is final. Questions about any particular decision may be asked privately.<br /><br />The dull stuff:<br /><br />For those concerned about such things, everything on this site is viewable by search engines. Posts are owned by the poster, but the forum owner reserves the right to publish them in any way that is desired. Edits may be made in the course of moderation. Post contents are the complete responsibility of the poster and the forum owner and moderators cannot be held responsible for any repercussions that may arise from them. Only one username per person allowed - if you think you have multiple voices, see a specialist.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">NickH</a> — Sun Jun 26, 2011 4:40 pm — Replies 0 — Views 320</p><hr />
]]></content>
